<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="translation">Translation</a> - The process of creating a <a href="#peptide">peptide</a> i.e. <a href="#protein">protein</a> (sequence of <a href="#amino_acid">amino acids</a>). <em>Exempli gratia</em> a <a href="#protein">protein</a> or <a href="#enzyme">enzyme</a>) based on the sequence of an <a href="#mrna">mRNA</a>. The <a href="#ribosome">ribosome</a> is the key <a href="#enzyme">enzyme</a> in this process, which also requires <a href="#tRNA">tRNA</a>s charged with <a href="#amino_acid">amino acids</a>. <a href="#amino_acid">Amino acids</a> are linked together through <a href="#protein">peptide bonds</a>.